{
  "stem": "27335.9",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at-- at one time in, in, in-- at the time, at the time, the Vietnam War, the peace movement here in Toronto called a meeting and a-- a-- a smaller meeting in the King Edward hotel on King-- on King Street, where Dr.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "James G.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Endicott, the leader of the Canadian peace movement, had a report from, from Vietnam and, and, and Korea, how the Americans used poison gas and, and [INAUDIBLE] bombs against the people there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he's going-- he's going to give, give a report in that meeting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I, myself, I, myself, served, served, served for, for this movement and so on security.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When we had visitors like dean of Canterbury from England, Paul Robeson from the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Endicott, the leader of the peace movement, [INAUDIBLE] from-- the leader of the Communist party.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So because of my war service and then the experience, I organized the security it needed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] was after these people, the right-winger and fascist and so.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And at this-- at this meeting, I was there, very first one, to look around the building and place people, you see, where to, where to [INAUDIBLE] and secure the, what you call them, the safety of the Dr.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Endicott.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this, this [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Wiesel ?] man showed up with a-- with a armful of-- armful of leaflets.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then they started to come, and apparently two Ukrainians came, from Ukrainian organization, who were in my, in my group.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We were in a security, what I told you, go inside, put your coat and hat-- hat on, and so.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And this man, who then turned out to be that I recognized later, handed a leaflet to them.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
